str2: But, except, however. Neuter plural of allos; properly, other things, i.e. contrariwise.
In order that, so that. Probably from the same as the former part of heautou; in order that.

str2: From dia and the base of nomos; to distribute, i.e. to disseminate.
Or neuter pleion, or pleon comparative of polus; more in quantity, number, or quality; also the major portion.
A primary preposition; to or into, of place, time, or purpose; also in adverbial phrases.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
Apparently a primary word; a people.

parse: Verb - Aorist Subjunctive Middle - 1st Person Plural
str2: To threaten, forbid by threatening. Of uncertain derivation; to menace; by implication, to forbid.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Dative Masculine 3rd Person Plural
str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.
A prolonged form of an otherwise obsolete verb; to talk, i.e. Utter words.
No longer, no more. From me and eti; no further.
On, to, against, on the basis of, at.
Name, character, fame, reputation. From a presumed derivative of the base of ginosko; a 'name'.
